==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Riant
<hw>Ri`ant"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>riant</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>rire</ets> to laugh, L.
<ets>ridere</ets>.]</ety> <def>Laughing; laughable; exciting gayety;
gay; merry; delightful to the view, as a landscape.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In such cases the sublimity must be drawn from the other sources,
with a strict caution, howewer, against anything light and
<qex>riant</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rib</ent>⟦br⟧
